 items in your cart shop vault guides vault guides are the source for insider insight on career information and employer reviews shop vault guides charter communications operating llc my vault overview employee reviews submit a review about charter communications operating llc faced with the choice of going big or remaining a lowertier cable player charter communications went big it became the  cable tv company in the us behind comcast with its  acquisitions of time warner cable and bright house networks for a total of some  billion the combined company serves about more than  million residential and commercial customers across the us it offers a full range of services to residential subscribers including cable tv highspeed internet voice over ip voip telephone and entertainment packages its services for businesses include internet access data networking phone and wireless backhaul charter chose spectrum as the brand name for the combined cable internet voice and business services operations most of charter communications’ revenue comes from the residential side of its operations with the rest provided by business services and advertising residential video services about  of revenue range from basic programming to premium channels as well as payperview and videoondemand it also offers digital video recording and its spectrum tv app provides subscribers access to tv service on mobile devices residential internet services about a third of revenue provide tiers of service based on the speed of the internet connection the highest is  megabits the company offers download speeds between  and  mbps charter’s residential voice services more than  of revenue use voip technology to transmit digital voice signals over its network voice services include unlimited local and long distance calling to the us canada mexico and puerto rico voicemail call waiting caller id call forwarding and other features in its business segment charter offers broadband communications for businesses and carriers including internet access data networking fiber connectivity to cellular towers and office buildings video entertainment services and business telephone services the services for small and medium businesses about  of revenue are similar to those for residential customers with the addition of web hosting email security and multiline telephone service for bigger businesses about  of revenue charter offers fiberdelivered communications and managed it solutions as well as highcapacity lastmile data connectivity services to wireless and wireline carriers internet service providers and other competitive carriers wholesale managed it offerings include cloud infrastructure as a service cloud desktop as a service managed hosting and messaging the company’s advertising sales division about  of revenue spectrum reach offers local regional and national businesses with the opportunity to advertise in individual and multiple markets on cable television networks charter also operates several regional sports and news networks geographic reach charter communications does business in some states covering the us from maine to hawaii and from the canadian border to the gulf of mexico the company’s five biggest regions are the west with more than  million customer relationships the northeast with more than  million central with about  million the carolinas with more than  million and texas with more than  million sales and marketing charter communications emphasizes its bundled services combinations of video internet and voice in its advertising and marketing efforts under the spectrum brand it has instituted a common set of pricing and packing for all it markets the company’s marketing organization manages the direct sales online outbound telemarketing and store channels it spends about  billion on marketing financial performance acquiring a couple of companies did wonders for charter communication’s top and bottom lines with the operations of time warner cable and bright house networks on board the company’s  revenue jumped nearly  to about  billion from just under  billion in  the company also posted a big profit after losing money in  charter saw increases in the number of residential internet and triple play customers and in commercial business customers it also reported revenue from higher equipment charges and rate increases the number of basic video customers declined although charter incurred higher expenses with the acquisitions the sales gusher propelled the company to net income of about  billion a turnaround from a loss of  million in  cash flow from operations rose to about  billion in  from about  billion in  boosted by a substantial increase in earnings before interest taxes debt and amortization strategy charter communications reached at least one goal with the acquisition of time warner cable and bright house communications it got a lot bigger it covers more ground and has more customers who bring in more revenue that helps charter battle a growing list of telecom competitors that includes other cable companies like comcast altice usa and cox communications satellite tv providers such as dishtv and directv owned by att and streaming service such as netflix and amazon prime the company’s size should help it win better deals with content providers when carrier contracts are renegotiated since the deal concluded in  charter has worked to integrate time warner and bright house into its operations the company branded the combined cable operations under the name spectrum and began the several year process of consolidating business practices and systems and it systems the company moved quickly to roll out standard products pricing and packaging across all regions a process completed in  common packaging of service bundles reduces the number of lowvalue products charter continued to be beset into  by high churn involving lowvalue time warner products that were offered at discounts to new and existing customers charter said it would not offer the same discounts to existing customers as it might to attract new customers charter also emphasizes customer experience as part of its strategy the company handles much of its customer service and field operations with its own workforce which it says results in higher quality service transactions charter is installing its model of virtualized call centers that allow calls to be routed to agents who can address specific problems in the time warner and bright house centers further the company built a call center in mcallen texas to serve spanishspeaking customers looking to the future charter is researching and testing technology and equipment for g networks which are to offer more capacity and higher speeds than current g and g networks mobile carriers are also working on g for mobile applications while charter is looking at applications such as virtual and augmented reality for a dwelling or office the company’s g services would work with its fiber and wifi networks which saves capital expenditures in building new network capacity beyond its planned efforts charter has partnered with verizon to offer its customers wireless phone service in  to help compete against companies like att and its dishtv offerings in mid charter and comcast discussed a similar arrangement with sprint what charter doesn’t have is content that could drive subscribers to use more of its services many customers have cut higher value cable video services while keeping the internet service and turned to overthetop entertainment providers such as netflix amazon and hulu other providers have bought content providers or created their own content mergers and acquisitions charters acquisition of time warner cable and bright house networks for about  billion made the company a credible competitor to industry leader comcast charter swept into buy time warner after comcasts proposed acquisition of time warner was scuttled by regulatory concerns time warner and bright house brought new geographies to charters operation including some in major cities in  arris group inc and charter acquired activevideo for approximately  million arris owns  of the joint venture company formed by arris and charter for the acquisition activevideo was the developer of cloudtv a cloudbased software platform enabling service providers content aggregators and consumer electronics manufacturers to rapidly deploy new services by virtualizing consumer premises equipment functions in the cloud company background driven by dreams of creating a wired world chairman paul allen a cofounder of microsoft reportedly poured more than  billion into charter since  and the billionaire saw most of that investment evaporate after expanding through the purchase of a slew of smalltown cable assets that needed extensive infrastructure upgrades charter experienced ongoing subscriber losses financial losses and a debt load in excess of  billion faced with legal opposition from some of its lenders the companys  bankruptcy reorganization plan eliminated about  billion of debt reduced annual interest expenses by about  million and left allen controlling about onethird of the company a stake that has since fallen to less than   show less  show full description  show less  show full history  show less  show all  show less  show all company news and press releases time warner cable subsidiaries seek dismissal of class action over allegedly unsolicited fax legalnewslinecom mon jul  moodys assigns ba rating to charter communications proposed notes issuance moodys investors service tue jun  charter offers senior secured notes pr newswire tue jun  emerson electric  us patents awarded to inventors in missouri june  traders sat jun  mks instruments  us patents awarded to inventors in colorado june  traders sat jun  chicago firm seeks to lead as plaintiff tcpa class action over fax legalnewslinecom tue may  charter announces first quarter  results tech news tmcnet tue may  commodifying words and letter